obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (36303)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00014_198710_1517807326889&sectionId=36303&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00014_198710_1517807326889
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Jute Packaging`
  line `Materials (Compulsory Use in Packing Commodities) Act, 1987.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force of such date ^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 14th May, 1987, vide notification No. S.O. 467(E), dated 14th May, 1987, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (36304)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00014_198710_1517807326889&sectionId=36304&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00014_198710_1517807326889
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "commodity" means--`
  line
  line `(i) any essential commodity;`
  line
  line `(ii) any article manufactured or produced by any scheduled industry;`
  line
  line `(b) "essential commodity" shall have the same meaning as in the Essential Commodities Act,`
  line `1955 (10 of 1955);`
  line
  line `(c) "jute packaging material" means jute, jute yarn, jute twine, jute sacking cloth, hessian cloth,`
  line `jute bags or any other packaging material containing not less than seventy-five per cent., by weight,`
  line `of jute;`
  line
  line `(d) "scheduled industry" shall have the same meaning as in the Industries (Development and`
  line `Regulation) Act, 1951 (65 of 1951);`
  line
  line `(e) "Standing Advisory Committee" means the Standing Advisory Committee constituted under`
  line `section 4.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (36305)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Power to specify commodities which are required to be packed in jute packaging material.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00014_198710_1517807326889&sectionId=36305&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00014_198710_1517807326889
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, the`
  line `Central Government may, if it is satisfied, after considering the recommendations made to it by the`
  line `Standing Advisory Committee, that it is necessary so to do in the interests of production of raw jute and`
  line `jute packaging material, and of persons engaged in the production thereof, by order published in the`
  line `Official Gazette, direct, from time to time, that such commodity or class of commodities or such`
  line `percentage thereof, as may be specified in the order, shall, on and from such date, as may be specified in`
  line `the order, be packed for the purposes of its supply or distribution in such jute packaging material as may`
  line `be specified in the order:`
  line
  line `Provided that until such time as the Standing Advisory Committee is constituted under section 4, the`
  line `Central Government shall, before making any order under this sub-section, consider the matters specified`
  line `in sub-section (2) of section 4, and any order so made shall cease to operate at the expiration of three`
  line `months from the date on which the Standing Advisory Committee makes its recommendations.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under sub-section (1) shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before`
  line `each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised`
  line `in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the order or both Houses agree that the order should not be made, the order shall thereafter have effect`
  line `only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification`
  line `or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that order.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (36306)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Constitution of Standing Advisory Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00014_198710_1517807326889&sectionId=36306&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00014_198710_1517807326889
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, with a view`
  line `to determining the commodity or class of commodities or percentages thereof in respect of which jute`
  line `packaging material shall be used in their packing, constitute a Standing Advisory Committee consisting of`
  line `such persons as have, in the opinion of that Government, the necessary expertise to give advice in the`
  line matter.
  line
  line `(2) The Standing Advisory Committee shall, after considering the following matters, indicate its`
  line `recommendations to the Central Government, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the existing level of usage of jute material;`
  line
  line `(b) the quantity of raw jute available;`
  line
  line `(c) the quantity of jute material available;`
  line
  line `(d) the protection of interests of persons engaged in the jute industry and in the production of raw`
  line jute;
  line
  line `(e) the need for continued maintenance of jute industry;`
  line
  line `(f) the quantity of commodities which, in its opinion, is likely to be required for packing in jute`
  line material;
  line
  line `(g) such other matters as the Standing Advisory Committee may think fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (36307)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Prohibition of packing in any material other than the jute packaging material.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00014_198710_1517807326889&sectionId=36307&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00014_198710_1517807326889
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Where an`
  line `order has been made under section 3 requiring any commodity, class of commodities or any percentage`
  line `thereof to be packed in jute packaging material for their supply or distribution, such commodity, class of`
  line `commodities or percentage thereof shall not, on and from the date specified in such order, be supplied or`
  line `distributed unless the same is packed in accordance with that order:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall apply to the supply or distribution of any commodity, class`
  line `of commodities or percentage thereof for a period of three months from the aforesaid date if immediately`
  line `before that date such commodity, class of commodities or percentage thereof, were being packed in any`
  line `material other than jute packing material.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (36308)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Power to call for information and samples.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00014_198710_1517807326889&sectionId=36308&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00014_198710_1517807326889
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by order, require`
  line `any person, who is required to use jute packaging material for packing under section 5, to furnish, for the`
  line `purposes of this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) such information in his possession, with respect to any commodity or class of commodities or`
  line `percentage thereof which requires such packing, to any officer specified by it, in such form and`
  line `within such period as may be specified by that Government in the order;`
  line
  line `(b) such samples of jute packaging material for inspection by such officer at such places and`
  line `within such period as may be specified by it in the order.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (36309)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Power to enter and inspect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00014_198710_1517807326889&sectionId=36309&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00014_198710_1517807326889
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Any officer authorised by the Central Government (hereinafter`
  line `referred to as the authorised officer) may enter, at all reasonable times, any place, premises or vehicle`
  line `where any commodity packed in jute packaging material is stored or kept for supply or distribution, and`
  line `may require its production for inspection and ask for any information relating thereto.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (36310)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Power to search and seize.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00014_198710_1517807326889&sectionId=36310&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00014_198710_1517807326889
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The authorised officer may, if he has reason to believe that any`
  line `commodity has been packed in contravention of section 5 and is secreted in any place, premises or`
  line `vehicle, enter into and search such place, premises or vehicle for such commodity.`
  line
  line `(2) Where, as a result of any search made under sub-section (1), any commodity packed in`
  line `contravention of section 5 has been found, the authorised officer may seize such commodity and any`
  line `other thing which, in his opinion, will be useful for, or relevant to, any proceeding under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that where it is not practicable to seize any such commodity or thing, the authorised officer`
  line `may serve on the person an order that he shall not remove, part with, or otherwise deal with, the`
  line `commodity or thing except with the previous permission of the authorised officer.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), relating to searches and`
  line `seizures shall, so far as may be, apply to every search or seizure made under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (36311)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Penalty for contravention of section 5.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00014_198710_1517807326889&sectionId=36311&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00014_198710_1517807326889
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `Whoever packs any commodity, class of commodities`
  line `or any percentage thereof in any material in contravention of section 5 shall be punishable with fine`
  line `which may extend to an amount equal to double the cost of the jute packaging material which should have`
  line `been used in accordance with the order made under section 3.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (36312)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Penalty for false statement, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00014_198710_1517807326889&sectionId=36312&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00014_198710_1517807326889
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `If any person, when required by any order made under section`
  line `6 to furnish any information or sample, fails to furnish such information or sample, or makes any`
  line `statement or furnishes any information which is false in any material particular and which he knows, or`
  line `has reasonable cause to believe, to be false or does not believe it to be true, he shall be punishable with`
  line `fine which may extend to five thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (36313)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00014_198710_1517807326889&sectionId=36313&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00014_198710_1517807326889
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person who, at the time the offence was committed, was in charge, of, and was`
  line `responsible to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shall`
  line `be deemed to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished`
  line `accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment provided in this Act, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or`
  line `that he had exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in this sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has`
  line `been committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be`
  line `guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (36314)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Offences to be cognizable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00014_198710_1517807326889&sectionId=36314&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00014_198710_1517807326889
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), every offence punishable under this Act shall be cognizable.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (36315)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Power to delegate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00014_198710_1517807326889&sectionId=36315&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00014_198710_1517807326889
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette,`
  line `direct that the powers exercisable by it under any provision of this Act, other than the power to make`
  line `orders under section 3 or under section 16 or to make rules under section 17, shall, in relation to such`
  line `matters and subject to such conditions, if any, as may be specified in the order, be exercisable also by--`
  line
  line `(a) such officer or authority subordinate to the Central Government; or`
  line
  line `(b) such State Government or such officer or authority subordinate to a State Government,`
  line
  line `as may be specified in the order.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (36316)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Central Government to give directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00014_198710_1517807326889&sectionId=36316&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00014_198710_1517807326889
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may give such directions as`
  line `it may consider necessary to a State Government as to the carrying into execution of the provisions of this`
  line Act.
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (36317)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00014_198710_1517807326889&sectionId=36317&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00014_198710_1517807326889
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the Central Government, State Government or any officer or employee of the Central`
  line `Government or of any State Government or any authorised officer for anything which is in good faith`
  line `done or intended to be done under this Act or any rule or order made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (36318)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Power to exempt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00014_198710_1517807326889&sectionId=36318&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00014_198710_1517807326889
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Central Government is of the opinion that it is necessary or`
  line `expedient so to do in the public interest, it may, by order published in the Official Gazette, exempt any`
  line `person or class of persons, supplying or distributing any commodity or class of commodities, from the`
  line `operation of an order made under section 3.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under sub-section (1) shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before`
  line `each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised`
  line `in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the order or both Houses agree that the order should not be made, the order shall thereafter have effect`
  line `only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification`
  line `or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that order.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (36319)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00014_198710_1517807326889&sectionId=36319&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00014_198710_1517807326889
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it`
  line `is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which`
  line `may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
